# Cloudflare Pages redirects file
# Replaces the "redirects" block from vercel.json
# Format: source  destination  status_code
# Cloudflare Pages natively handles clean URLs and .html stripping,
# so the vercel.json "rewrites" block is not needed here.

# www → apex 301 redirect (DEF-008)
# Layer 1: Cloudflare Dashboard > DNS > CNAME www → crowagent.ai (CF Pages
# automatically 301-redirects the www custom domain to the apex). Layer 2:
# Cloudflare Rules > Redirect Rules (Match host = www.crowagent.ai → 301
# concat("https://crowagent.ai", http.request.uri.path)). Layer 3 (this file —
# defense in depth): pages-level _redirects splat. Single direction only;
# no apex→www counterpart configured anywhere, so loops are not possible.
https://www.crowagent.ai/*  https://crowagent.ai/:splat  301!

# Directory rewrites — RESTORED 2026-05-06 11:35 UTC (DEF-LOOP-001).
# The earlier removal (WEB-AUDIT-001..010 in PR #148) inverted the actual root
# cause: without these 200-rewrites, CF Pages bidirectional 308-bounces
# `/foo` ↔ `/foo/` (real-world ERR_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS observed on prod after
# PR #148 merged). Each route has a corresponding /:slug/index.html on disk.
